The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 November is 8,265 (956.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 November, there were 1,053 new confirmed cases (121.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 November, there were 913 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 15% ( 140 extra cases).
